main event: A radar/visual sighting of a very bright object at a high altitude on February 13, 1961.
interesting points: The object was observed for almost 30 minutes, although insufficient information was available regarding its color, elevation, or direction change., The sighting was categorized as a radar/visual type., The report indicated that the object was much higher and appeared to be approaching., Communication about the sighting was relayed through multiple military channels., The object was moving toward an aircraft during the report.
sighted object: a very bright object in the sky
witness description: pilot in flight near the object
